World number-one Pete Sampras reached a  quarter-final showdown with old rival Jim Courier at the French Open here on  Sunday when he defeated astonishing Swedish qualifier Mikael Tillstrom 6-4,  6-4, 1-6, 6-4.
Tillstrom, the world's 226th-ranked player, was cheered off the new Roland  Garros 'A' court after pushing the top-seed close to the limit.
Sampras needed to save four break points in the eighth game of the fourth  set before clinching his win.
Earlier Courier beat Frenchman Olivier Delaitre in four sets.
